record.detail:
University of Adelaide Archives Series 1020 - 'The Student' Magazine of Roseworthy Agricultural College, 1897-1988: -Vol 20 No 1 July 1920, http://hdl.handle.net/2440/74013
-Vol 34 No1 1938, p 86, http://hdl.handle.net/2440/74196
NLA, TROVE1930, http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article147073394 NLA TROVE 1940 http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article147035469 NLA TROVE 1946 http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article200109331

From 1920 onwards, Mr Grieve stationed himself at Naracoorte. He had a property and raised sheep for wool. In 1930 his farm and livestock was offered for sale. in 1935, the Roseworthy magazine reported he was residing in Naracoorte. In 1938 the Student magazine reported he had a property in Naracoorte. His farming activities were disrupted in 1940 when he enlisted to serve in the army. His farm and animals were offered up to sale in 1940. Post WWII, he probably resumed sheep raising, there was newspaper advertisement of merino wool for sale from his farm at Naracoorte.

record.title: Colgan, T.D. (Thomas Dominic)

detail.name: OCRd book entry or other narrative

record.detail: Not listed in the Book of Remembrance or Sydney Teacher's College Rolls. He enlisted in March 1917 and served with the 6th A.L.H. Regiment and at Amman with 2nd M.G. Squadron. Wounded at Amman 28th March 1918 and invalided to hospital. Was demobilised in August 1919. Joined Sydney Teacher's College in 1920.

record.title: Cornford, H.W. (Harold Walton)

detail.name: OCRd book entry or other narrative

record.detail: Not listed in the Book of Remembrance or Sydney Teacher's College Rolls. Enlisted 4th January 1915, and joined H.M.A. Training ship "Tingira". Sailed as Boy 1st Class on H.M.A.S. "Encounter". Served at Fantome Una, Melbourne, Brisbane, Marguerite, Platypus, Destroyer Flotilla, Sydney and Sleuth. Tookk part in the Malekula punitive Expedition. Was demobilised 31st December, 1924. Rejoined Teaching Service and mobilised as Petty Officer in Charge of Communications convoy.

record.title: Grieve, A.C. (Alexander Clayhills)
record.detail: Upon graduation, Mr Grieve was active in Naracoorte.1920 he was raising sheep; in 1924 he was working with the firm of DeGaris, livestock agents in Naracoorte. In 1930 he sold his property and livestock,but throughout 1930s and beyond,he was offering livestock and sheep wool for sale. He operated from Naracoorte. He was also active in Golf and the Caledonian Society. Source - Trove digitised newspapers.
Finance Committee 1918-19, RAC 1938 - Committee member, South Eastern Sub-branch, Roseworthy Old Collegian' Association
